POLIOMYELITIS UPDATE (68): GLOBAL WILD POLIOVIRUS AND CIRCULATING VACCINE-DERIVED POLIOVIRUS, BENIN FIRST REPORT
****************************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 15 Aug 2019
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative / WHO [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus weekly update as of 14 Aug 2019, World Health Organization
-----------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 5
Environment: 8

Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2019: 65
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 33

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 7
Environment: 1
Others: 5

Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2019: 51
Total number of cVDPV cases (all types) in 2018: 104

Headlines
Summary of new viruses this week:
Afghanistan -- 3 wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1)-positive environmental samples;
Pakistan -- 5 WPV1 cases and 5 WPV1-positive environmental samples;
Nigeria -- 2 circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases, 1 cVDPV2-positive environmental sample;
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) -- 2 cVDPV2 cases;
Angola -- 2 cVDPV2 cases;
Benin -- 1 cVDPV2 case.

Afghanistan
- No WPV1 case has been reported in the past week. There are 12 WPV1 cases reported in 2019. There were 21 WPV1 cases reported in 2018.
- 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week: 2 from Kandahar district, Kandahar province, and 1 from Lashkargarh, Hilmand province. The samples were collected on [24 Jul 2019].

Pakistan
- 5 WPV1 cases were reported in the past week: 3 from Bannu district and 1 from Charsadda district, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, and 1 from South Waziristan, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. All cases had onset of paralysis in July 2019. There are 53 WPV1 cases in 2019, and 12 WPV1 cases were reported in 2018. [These cases were reported in Poliomyelitis update (66): Pakistan (KP) 20190807.6610623 - Mod.MPP]
- 5 WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week: 1 each from Lahore, Multan, and Faisalabad districts, Punjab province; 1 from Landhi Town, Karachi district, Sindh province; and 1 from Quetta district, Balochistan province. The samples were collected between [17 and 20 Jul 2019].

Nigeria, Lake Chad and West Africa
Nigeria
- 2 cases of cVDPV2 were reported in the past week: 1 each from Ankpa and Ibaji districts, Kogi State. The onsets of paralysis were on [13 and 20 Jun 2019]. There are 16 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2019. There were 34 cVDPV2 cases in 2018.
- 1 cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week from Ilorin East, Kwara State. The sample was collected on [13 Jul 2019].

Lake Chad
- No case of cVDPV2 has been reported in the past week.
- In the Lake Chad region, cVDPV2 linked to the outbreak originating in Nigeria has been detected in Niger (1 case in 2019 and 10 cases in 2018), and Cameroon (1 positive environmental sample, collected on [20 Apr 2019] in Extreme Nord).
The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across the Lake Chad subregion remains high.

West Africa: Benin and Ghana
- 1 cVDPV2 case was reported in the past week in Benin in Kalale district, Borgou State, with onset of paralysis on [7 Jul 2019] outbreak in Nigeria [??? -- perhaps this sentence referred to the virus being genetically related to an outbreak in Nigeria. - Mod.MPP]. This is the 1st-ever cVDPV case reported in Benin.
- No cVDPV2-positive environmental sample was reported in the past week. One cVDPV2-positive environmental [case] had previously been reported from Ghana, linked to virus circulating in Nigeria.
- Surveillance is being strengthened in neighbouring Togo, Cote d'Ivoire and Burkina Faso.
- The risk of further cVDPV2 spread across West Africa remains high.

Central Africa
Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
- 2 cases of cVDPV2 have been reported this week: 1 each from Mukanga and Wembo-Nyama districts in Haut Lomami and Sankuru provinces, respectively. There are 17 reported cases of cVDPV2 in 2019. There were 20 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2018. The DRC is currently affected by 9 separate cVDPV2 outbreaks: 1 each originated in Haut Katanga, Mongala, Sankuru, Tanganika, Tshopo, Kasai, Kasai Central, and 2 in Haut Lomami provinces.

Angola
- 2 cases of cVDPV2 have been reported this week in Zacaria Amando and Xa Muteba districts, Lunda Norte State. The onsets of paralysis were on 1 and 21 Jun 2019. There are a total of 5 cVDPV2 cases from 3 outbreaks reported in 2019.

Central African Republic (CAR)
- There are 4 reported cases from 4 different outbreaks of cVDPV2 in 2019. Additional confirmed cVDPV2 community contacts have been reported in CAR.
- No environmental samples were reported.

Horn of Africa
- No case of cVDPV2 has been reported in the past week.
- Somalia has reported a total of 15 cVDPV cases (8 type 2, 6 type 3 and 1 coinfection of both type 2 and type 3) since the beginning of the outbreaks. The most recent cVDPV3 virus was from an AFP case from Runingod district, Middle Shabelle province with an onset date of paralysis on [7 Sep 2018]. cVDPV2 has also been detected during 2018 in one environmental sample in Kenya collected on [21 Mar 2018]. There is also one reported case of cVDPV2 in Ethiopia, linked to Somalia, with onset on 20 May 2019.

Papua New Guinea
- No new cases of cVDPV1 were reported this week. There were 26 cases reported in 2018.

Mozambique
- No case of cVDPV2 outbreak has been reported this week. There was one case reported in 2018.

Indonesia
- No cVDPV1 cases were reported this week. One cVDPV1 case was reported in 2018 from Papua province with onset of paralysis on [28 Nov 2018].
- This outbreak is not linked to the cVDPV1 in neighbouring Papua New Guinea.

Iran
- No new WPV1-positive environmental samples were reported in the past week. In total, 3 WPV1-positive environmental samples have been reported in 2019, all from Sistan and Balochistan province. The isolated viruses have been detected in environmental samples only, and genetic sequencing confirms they are linked to WPV1 circulating in Karachi, Pakistan.

China
- No cVDPV2 cases were reported in the past week. The total number of cVDPV2 cases in the country remains one.

Myanmar
- No case of cVDPV1 has been reported. There are 3 reported cases of cVDPV1 in 2019.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 13 Aug 2019:
Total global cases in 2019: 65 (compared with 14 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in endemic countries in 2019: 65 (compared with 14 for the same period in 2018)
- Total in nonendemic countries in 2019: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018)

- Afghanistan: 12 cases in 2019 (compared with 11 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 26 May 2019
- Pakistan: 53 cases in 2019 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Jul 2019
- Nigeria: 0 case in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Aug 2016

Total global WPV1 cases in 2019: 65
Total global WPV1 cases in 2018: 33

Officially reported cVDPV cases as of 13 Aug 2019:
- Angola: 5 cases in 2019 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2018), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Jun 2019
